    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "This is actually expected with how Vue works. If you don't add a `:` before the attribute, `.camel` has no effect, and will be part of the attribute as-is. The correct behaviour would be what you wrote in the issue already (but not in the sandbox for some reason).\r\n\r\nsee: https://codesandbox.io/s/gallant-morning-gfziw1\r\n\r\n```vue\r\n<ais-configure\r\n  :hits-per-page.camel=\"4\"\r\n  :attributes-to-snippet.camel=\"['content', 'title']\"\r\n  :click-analytics.camel=\"true\"\r\n  :facet-filters.camel=\"facetFilters\"\r\n/>\r\n```\r\n\r\nI'll close the issue for now, but if you have a new reproduction, we'll take a look at it!",
